      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/go-monitoring-htmx/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;go-monitoring-htmx&#34;&gt;&#xA;  go-monitoring-htmx&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#go-monitoring-htmx&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Monitoring Dynamic Data from Server/PC and get also Weather/Crypto infromation real time with GO, HTMX and Websocket.. Data refreshs 5secs automatically&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;//localhost:1313/pic-selected-250415-2356-22.png&#34; alt=&#34;preview&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Code&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#code&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mozkaya1/go-monitoring-htmx&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;mozkaya1@github.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;real-time-data&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Real Time Data&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#real-time-data&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Current Time&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Below feed is coming from my another go-api service.. It can be adjusted what you need with changing api url/query on internal/api/btc.go file. Details also on &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mozkaya1/go-api#&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;go-api&lt;/a&gt; repo page.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
